   <body>
      <p>The <uicontrol>Math</uicontrol> operations enable you to add numbers into the
logic or to execute arithmetic operations in the logic.</p>
      <p>
         <uicontrol>Number Block</uicontrol>
      </p>
      <p>The Number block enables you  to use a number field in the logic. For
example, if you want to check if the value of a field is greater than a value, then you can use the Number block.</p>
      <p>
         <uicontrol>Arithmetic Operations Block</uicontrol>
      </p>
      <p>The Arithmetic Operations block enables you to execute arithmetic operations. This block has an input operand and an output block. For
example, if you want to check whether a field value is greater than 30% of another field value, then you can use the Arithmetic Operations block.<fig>
            <title/>
            <image href="../../../Icons/Screenshots_Icons/Arithmetic_Operations_block.jpg"
                   placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </p>
